PASSWORD RESET GUIDE

How to Reset Your Password

Option 1: Self-Service Reset
1. Go to the login page and click "Forgot Password".
2. Enter your registered email address.
3. Check your inbox for a password reset email (check spam if not received within 5 minutes).
4. Click the reset link — it is valid for 30 minutes.
5. Enter and confirm your new password.
6. Log in with your new credentials.

Option 2: Admin-Initiated Reset
- Account admins can reset passwords from the Admin Panel > Users > [Select User] > Reset Password.
- The user will receive an email with a temporary password.

Password Requirements
- Minimum 8 characters
- At least one uppercase letter
- At least one number
- At least one special character (e.g., !, @, #, $)

Security Tips
- Do not reuse previous passwords.
- Use a password manager to generate and store strong passwords.
- Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) for additional security.

Locked Accounts
- Accounts are locked after 5 consecutive failed login attempts.
- Locked accounts are automatically unlocked after 15 minutes.
- Contact support if you need an immediate unlock.

For further assistance, contact support@example.com.
